Doveguard is a lightweight log-watcher for Dovecot on FreeBSD. It tails the
mail log, counts repeated authentication failures within a configurable window,
and automatically bans abusive IPs by updating PF or IPFW tables. The daemon is
written in Rust with no external dependencies beyond the base system, so it fits
well on small jails or embedded appliances.

Doveguard targets FreeBSD specifically and does not rely on blacklistd. Linux
support would require a different firewall backend and is not part of this
release.
